-- BlueCrests’s Platt Says Eurobonds Needed If Greece Leaves Euro
-- B y   J e s s e   W e s t b r o o k   a n d   S t e p h a n i e   R u h l e
-- 2012-05-21T11:39:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-21/bluecrests-s-platt-says-eurobonds-needed-if-greece-leaves-euro.html
Michael Platt, the founder of $32
billion hedge fund BlueCrest Capital Management LLP, said Europe
will likely have to issue bonds backing the entire region to
stem the financial crisis that would follow a Greek exit.  “There would need to be an enormous announcement from the
EU,” Platt said in an interview today on Bloomberg Television’s
